\frac{(40)(99!)}{100!},
\mathbb{P}(\mbox{15th ball is red})={1\over (100)_{15}}\sum_k {14\choose k} (40)_{15-k}\ (60)_k 
={1\over (100)_{15}}\ 40\ \sum_k{14\choose k} (39)_{14-k}\ (60)_k ={1\over (100)_{15}}\ 40\ (99)_{14} ={40\over 100}.
